name: CGPathFillRule
desc: Rules for determining which regions are interior to a path, used by the fillPath(using:) and clip(using:) methods.

items.name: case evenOdd
items.desc: A rule that considers a region to be interior to a path based on the number of times it is enclosed by path elements.

items.name: case winding
items.desc: A rule that considers a region to be interior to a path if the winding number for that region is nonzero.

items.name: static func != (CGPathFillRule, CGPathFillRule) -> Bool
items.desc: Returns a Boolean value indicating whether two values are not equal.
